article.headline: Cleveland St. 74, Wis.-Milwaukee 64
article.story: CLEVELAND, Ohio (AP) -- Cedric Jackson scored 18 points and had nine rebounds to lead Cleveland State to a 74-64 win over visiting Wisconsin-Milwaukee on Wednesday night. Norris Cole added 14 points and J'Nathan Bullock contributed 13 for the Vikings, who had four players score in the double figures and led the entire game. Deion James had 18 points to lead Milwaukee (13-12, 8-7 Horizon League), while Marcus Skinner, Paige Paulsen and Deonte Roberts each had 11 points. Cleveland State (18-11, 11-6) shot just over 49 percent from the field, while Milwaukee shot nearly 44 percent. Cleveland State saw its largest lead of 14 with 11:36 to go in the second half.
